Police Commissioner Elias Mawela is leading the crackdown on hijacked vehicles, brothels and suspected drug dens. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Over 30 people have been arrested at a Sandton roadblock on Thursday morning, as law enforcement authorities crackdown on crime hotspots in Gauteng. Africa’s richest square mile is on the police’s radar for hijackings, business crimes and burglaries. READ: Three arrested for Zandspruit mob attack eNCA’s senior reporter Aviwe Mtila shares more details in the video above.